description.narrative: Good progress has been made in the development of national learning assessment systems with the completion of training for the Ministry of Education (MoE) dedicated team and with the planning of a first assessment on second, third, fourth and seventh grades to be conducted in 2020. A UNICEF-supported capacity building sessions on result-based management have been initiated for MoE key staff to reinforce the overall governance and to achieve an equitable and inclusive access and quality education for all. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:29/12/2019
